👉 Just remember:

1st----> cd /usr/src/linux-headers-$(uname -r)/
2nd----> example:- jambaliya@39172--VISN--AHM:/usr/src/linux-headers-6.8.0-106-generic$------>  grep -rn "chrdev" 

kernel headers → /usr/src/linux-headers-$(uname -r)

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

2. Learn Folder Meaning (Not Exact Path)

--------------------------------------------------------------------|
Folder		|	What it Contains                            |
--------------------------------------------------------------------| 
include/linux/	|	Header files (macros, APIs) ⭐		    |
fs/		|	File system & char device code  	    |
drivers/	|	Actual drivers				    |
kernel/		|	Core kernel logic  			    |
Documentation/	|	Explanations                                |
---------------------------------------------------------------------



